Title: Application Development Specialist – Residential Construction
Job_Description:
Location: Midland, MI
Skills: Residential Construction Industry, Construction Practices, Building Physics, Building Code, Civil Engineering, Construction Management
OVERVIEW
We are seeking for a Applications Development Specialist for our Water & Protection’s (W&P) Shelter business that combines market-leading brands (including Corian® Design, Great Stuff™, Styrofoam™ and Tyvek®) into one customer-centric line of business. Performance Building Solutions (PBS), as business unit within S&C Shelter, is a leading global provider of value-added solutions in the areas of weatherization, air sealing, thermal comfort and fire protection systems for the building and construction market. PBS is an active leader in advancing building science, developing solutions to improve construction productivity and fostering the use of more sustainable and resilient building materials and practices.

Title: Application Development Specialist – Residential Construction
Job_Description:
We are seeking for a Applications Development Specialist for our Water & Protection’s (W&P) Shelter business that combines market-leading brands (including Corian® Design, Great Stuff™, Styrofoam™ and Tyvek®) into one customer-centric line of business. Performance Building Solutions (PBS), as business unit within S&C Shelter, is a leading global provider of value-added solutions in the areas of weatherization, air sealing, thermal comfort and fire protection systems for the building and construction market. PBS is an active leader in advancing building science, developing solutions to improve construction productivity and fostering the use of more sustainable and resilient building materials and practices.
The Applications Development Team plays a key role in developing and executing test plans to expand viable applications for existing products, to qualify new products and to demonstrate products meet building code requirements. The team works closely with Strategic Marketing, Tactical Marketing, the Building Knowledge Center (BKC) and the Advocacy teams to address complex customer inquiries and to develop advantaged industry positions for PBS.

Title: Weekend Open-Source Intelligence Analyst
Job_Description:
Barbaricum is a rapidly growing government contractor providing leading-edge support to federal customers, with a particular focus on Defense and National Security mission sets. We leverage more than 14 years of support to stakeholders across the federal government, with established and growing capabilities across Intelligence, Analytics, Engineering, Mission Support, and Communications disciplines. Founded in 2008, our mission is to transform the way our customers approach constantly changing and complex problem sets by bringing to bear the latest in technology and the highest caliber of talent.

Headquartered in Washington, DC's historic Dupont Circle neighborhood, Barbaricum also has a corporate presence in Tampa, FL and Dayton, OH, with team members across the United States and around the world. As a leader in our space, we partner with firms in the private sector, academic institutions, and industry associations with a goal of continually building our expertise and capabilities for the benefit of our employees and the customers we support. Through all of this, we have built a vibrant corporate culture diverse in expertise and perspectives with a focus on collaboration and innovation. Our teams are at the frontier of the Nation's most complex and rewarding challenges. Join us.

NAU Strategic Initiatives and Operations is seeking one (1) skilled and experienced Business Analyst or to join our team. This position develops and maintains an understanding of Student Affairs needs and their alignment with business goals and objectives. Elicits business needs from subject matter experts, translates needs into functional requirements, and documents requirements in specifications, business process flows, analysis tools, etc. Evaluates past and current department-level business processes and data to improve decision-making within the department. Collaborates with business partners and stakeholders to identify goals, best practices, and other methods for gathering and analyzing processes, business applications, and data. Contributes to aspects of complex projects. Collaborates as a member of an institutional center of excellence with enterprise business analysts and other divisional business analysts at the institution. Helps to identify the Student Affairs business intelligence, reporting, and data analysis needs. Assists Student Affairs in developing a picture of the divisions’ current contributions and new efforts to improve student retention and academic success, wellness, and inclusion/sense of belonging.

Title: R&D Applications Data Engineer- Hybrid
Job_Description:
Introduction
About DuPont Corporate Functions
To be the best science company in the world, we need more than scientists. We need passionate people who are the best at finance, human resources, law, logistics, and so much more. While we’re deeply rooted in science, DuPont careers span a wide range of skills and disciplines. Our teams are focused on achieving the best results for our customers and the business. They're inspired by innovation, excited by collaboration, and strive to achieve more agile ways of moving the business forward. Learn more about us here: https://www.dupont.com
The Role and Responsibilities
The DuPont Information Technology Team at the Spruance location provides leveraged operational support for all aspects of IT infrastructure and to all the businesses and functions at the site. This position will provide network and technical support through the execution of incidents, request management, problem, and policies/procedures. Other duties include diagnosis, troubleshooting and tracking of incidents/requests; report status and system outage notifications to customers, technical staff, and applicable management entities; maintaining a robust, accurate knowledge base and inventory repositories. Develop, design, maintain, enhance, and implement networks, systems, and equipment. Analyze existing networks and equipment and provides opportunities for improvement. Work with cross-functional teams to develop and implement solutions to meet business requirements.

Introduction
About DuPont Corporate Functions
To be the best science company in the world, we need more than scientists. We need passionate people who are the best at finance, human resources, law, logistics, and so much more. While we’re deeply rooted in science, DuPont careers span a wide range of skills and disciplines. Our teams are focused on achieving the best results for our customers and the business. They're inspired by innovation, excited by collaboration, and strive to achieve more agile ways of moving the business forward. Learn more about us here: https://www.dupont.com
The Role and Responsibilities
The DuPont Information Technology Team at the Spruance location provides leveraged operational support for all aspects of IT infrastructure and to all the businesses and functions at the site. This position will provide network and technical support through the execution of incidents, request management, problem, and policies/procedures. Other duties include diagnosis, troubleshooting and tracking of incidents/requests; report status and system outage notifications to customers, technical staff, and applicable management entities; maintaining a robust, accurate knowledge base and inventory repositories. Develop, design, maintain, enhance, and implement networks, systems, and equipment. Analyze existing networks and equipment and provides opportunities for improvement. Work with cross-functional teams to develop and implement solutions to meet business requirements.

Title: Senior Computer Engineer
Job_Description: The Quality Engineer for Yerkes Tedlar® is responsible for maintaining and improving our vision systems that inspect Tedlar® Film. This includes a continuous web inspection (CWI) and optical crease detection (OCD). The Quality Engineer will drive improvements in disposition of product to ensure that timely feedback is given to the operations team on the status of current production. The Quality Engineer will also look to improve the capabilities of the vision systems to detect defects that customers find objectionable. Additionally, the Quality Engineer for Yerkes Tedlar® is responsible for supporting the quality management system, customer satisfaction, quality certifications, quality related aspects of supplier and contract manufacturer relationship, training, quality audits, corrective and preventive action, development of a quality culture and drive continuous quality improvement within the manufacturing organization which also includes the laboratories. This includes tactical execution of quality initiatives and managing activities at the Yerkes Tedlar® plant in Buffalo, NY. The role will provide guidance for all supporting functions on the quality assurance process including the QMS in SAP, customer complaint investigations and continuous improvement initiatives. The role manages the quality systems (primarily the vision systems), and requirements to assure compliance. Evaluates data using statistical methodology and monitors compliance with customer specifications. Uses significant process experience and quality knowledge and training to make appropriate business-based decisions. This role will report to the Yerkes Tedlar Engineering Science Leader.

Title: Senior Computer Engineer
Job_Description:
About BDP International:
BDP International is a privately held, family-owned non-asset based global logistics provider with annual sales exceeding $2.1 billion USD. Founded in 1966 by Richard Bolte Sr. and based in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, BDP has grown to be one of the largest logistics providers in the world. BDP employs more than 3,900 people worldwide, and operates freight logistics centers in 270 cities across the world through a global network of wholly owned offices, joint ventures and affiliates in 135 countries.
The company serves more than 4,000 customers worldwide. Clients include Bayer, Dow, DuPont, Heineken USA, Honeywell, Johnson & Johnson, Revlon, Trek Bicycle, Wacker, and others.

Title: Senior Computer Engineer
Job_Description:
As we create a colorful, capable and cleaner world through chemistry, we invite you to join our team to harness the power of chemistry to shape markets, redefine industries and improve lives for billions of people around the world.
The Chemours Corpus Christi site (previously known as the DuPont site) located in Ingleside, TX has a position available for an Electrical & Instrumentation (E&I) Reliability Engineer. This position will report to the Site Maintenance and Reliability Manager. The Chemours Corpus Christi site is part of the Thermal and Specialized Solutions business and focuses on the production of Opteon TM and Freon TM refrigerants. The site is a key asset in the Chemours supply chain for the Thermal and Specialized Solutions business.
This role will serve as the E&I Reliability Engineer for all assets at this facility. The individual will provide overall E &I Reliability support for the site Operations, Maintenance, and Technology Teams. The E&I Reliability Engineer will drive equipment failures to root cause using a team-based approach. The successful candidate is expected to provide timely, accurate analyses and recommendations for acute issues, as well as develop long term strategies for defect elimination and improved operations. The successful candidate will be self-motivated, able to quickly develop skills and knowledge in new areas, and comfortable working simultaneously on multiple programs.

Title: Information Assurance Specialist - Naval Surface Warfare Center
Job_Description:
Requisition ID: 258132
Requisition Posting End Date: 11/21/2022
Project Overview:
Bechtel Parsons Blue Grass is the systems contractor selected by the Department of Defense’s Assembled Chemical Weapons Alternatives program to design, build, systemize, test, operate, and close a facility to destroy the chemical weapons stockpile at the Blue Grass Army Depot in Richmond, Kentucky.

The Blue Grass Chemical Agent-Destruction Pilot Plant (BGCAPP) will safely destroy 523 tons of mustard and nerve agent in projectiles and rockets. Neutralization followed by supercritical water oxidation is the technology selected by the Department of Defense to destroy the nerve agent, while the Explosive Destruction Technology will be used to destroy the mustard in the Blue Grass chemical weapons stockpile.

What you'll do...

Ensures area of responsibility is maintained in accordance with Company policies and procedures by properly handling returns; zoning the area; arranging and organizing merchandise; and identifying shrink and damages.

Provides member service by maintaining exit areas; reviewing member receipts; acknowledging the member and identifying member needs; assisting members with purchasing decisions; assisting members with locating merchandise.

Provides member service by maintaining self-checkout area; resolving member issues and concerns; promoting Sam's Club products and services; providing guidance and support to members regarding self-service technology; processing member purchases; assisting with payments, returns, refunds, and exchanges according to company policies and procedures for different membership and payment types; assisting members with transactions utilizing self-checkout area.

Assists with securing and safeguarding Sam's Club assets and property by observing and communicating potential criminal activity according to company policies and procedures; maintaining paperwork, logs, and other required documentation; executing emergency response procedures; and ensuring compliance with company security and safety practices.

Assists with the training of Member Frontline Service associates on company processes and procedures; teaching new technology and tool functionality; delivering new program rollout training; and providing continuous learning and process improvement opportunities.

Complies with company policies, procedures, and standards of ethics and integrity by implementing related action plans; using the Open Door Policy; and applying these in executing business processes and practices.

Completes work assignments and priorities by using policies, data, and resources; collaborating with managers, co-workers, customers, and other business partners; identifying priorities, deadlines, and expectations; carrying out tasks; communicating progress and information; determining and recommending ways to address improvement opportunities; and adapting to and learning from change, difficulties, and feedback.



Outlined below are the required minimum qualifications for this position. If none are listed, there are no minimum qualifications.



Outlined below are the optional preferred qualifications for this position. If none are listed, there are no preferred qualifications.

Customer Service, Retail experience including operating front end equipment (for example, cash register), Working with mobile retail applications

Title: Information Assurance Specialist - Naval Surface Warfare Center
Job_Description:
Barbaricum is a rapidly growing government contractor providing leading-edge support to federal customers, with a particular focus on Defense and National Security mission sets. We leverage more than 14 years of support to stakeholders across the federal government, with established and growing capabilities across Intelligence, Analytics, Engineering, Mission Support, and Communications disciplines. Founded in 2008, our mission is to transform the way our customers approach constantly changing and complex problem sets by bringing to bear the latest in technology and the highest caliber of talent.

Headquartered in Washington, DC's historic Dupont Circle neighborhood, Barbaricum also has a corporate presence in Tampa, FL and Dayton, OH, with team members across the United States and around the world. As a leader in our space, we partner with firms in the private sector, academic institutions, and industry associations with a goal of continually building our expertise and capabilities for the benefit of our employees and the customers we support. Through all of this, we have built a vibrant corporate culture diverse in expertise and perspectives with a focus on collaboration and innovation. Our teams are at the frontier of the Nation's most complex and rewarding challenges. Join us.

Title: Data Scientist/Engineer
Job_Description:
Why join us?
While we’re deeply rooted in science, DuPont careers span a wide range of skills and disciplines. Our purpose is to empower the world with essential innovations to thrive. We work on things that matter - whether it’s providing clean water to more than a billion people on the planet, producing materials that are essential in everyday technology devices from smartphones to electric vehicles, or protecting workers in this global pandemic. Have the Opportunity to chart your own course, challenge yourself, and acquire new capabilities to build a rewarding and fulfilling career. Learn more about us here: https://www.dupont.com
Role
DuPont Electronics & Industrial business has an exciting and challenging opportunity for a Data Scientist/Engineering in DuPont’s Electronic Materials Chemical Mechanical Planarization (CMP) Technology group located in . We are the global leader in making various consumables used to polish semiconductor wafers, which then becomes logics and memories in electronic devices, such as smart phones, computers, data center, etc.
